<item>
            <title>[PIG-2084] pig is running validation for a statement at a time batch mode, instead of running it for whole script</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2084</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2059&quot; title=&quot;PIG doesn&amp;#39;t validate incomplete query in batch mode even if -c option is given&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-2059&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-2059&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, a change was made to run validation for each statement instead of running it once for the whole script.&lt;br/&gt;
This slows down the validation phase, and it ends up taking tens of seconds.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12507906">PIG-2084</key>
            <summary>pig is running validation for a statement at a time batch mode, instead of running it for whole script</summary>
